  "prompt": "Who are IAS Aspirants?",
  "response": "IAS aspirants are individuals who are preparing to take the Indian Administrative Service (IAS) examination, which is conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) of India. The IAS is one of the premier civil services in India, and it is a prestigious career choice for many due to its significant responsibilities in governance, administration, and public service.\n\nThe IAS examination is known for its rigorous selection process, which typically includes three stages: \n\n1. **Preliminary Examination**: This is an objective type test consisting of two papers \u2014 General Studies and Civil Services Aptitude Test (CSAT).\n\n2. **Mains Examination**: This stage includes nine papers, which are descriptive in nature. Candidates must write essays, answer questions on various subjects, and present their knowledge and analytical abilities.\n\n3. **Interview (Personality Test)**: Candidates who qualify the Mains Examination are called for a personal interview, where their personality, communication skills, and suitability for a career in administrative services are assessed.\n\nIAS aspirants usually come from diverse educational backgrounds and spend months or even years preparing for the examination. They often enroll in coaching institutes, study various subjects, and keep abreast of current affairs to enhance their chances of success in this highly competitive exam.",
